1
00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:06,000
National Radio and Television Administration.

2
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,720
As long as Xiaobao is fine,

3
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,410
I'm okay with anything.

4
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:44,360
Yes, that's definitely right.

5
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:46,880
Look, the situation is like this now.

6
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,520
In the future, this child will

7
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:50,580
be taken care of by his sister, right?

8
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:53,039
Well, it's like this.

9
00:01:53,039 --> 00:01:53,920
No matter when you

10
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:57,000
or your mother want to see the child in the future,

11
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,690
just let us know in advance.

12
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:00,850
After you tell us in advance, we can

13
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:03,120
create time and opportunity for you.

14
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:04,440
That works.

15
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,800
As long as my mother can fulfill her wish,

16
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:10,410
I'll do whatever you ask. That's fine.

17
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,680
Sounds good now.

18
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,960
Come on, let's go inside.

19
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,960
Time to sleep.

20
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:24,440
Well then,

21
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,040
I'll be straightforward.

22
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:27,800
Is there anything

23
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,200
you two need my help with?

24
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:30,840
I actually

25
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:34,520
don't know how to tell you right now.

26
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:35,600
It's nothing.

27
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,780
You've already helped me so much.

28
00:02:38,079 --> 00:02:40,960
If I don't do something in return,

29
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,640
I'd feel uncomfortable about it.

30
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,040
Alright, I'll just say it directly.

31
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:44,600
Go ahead.

32
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,280
Actually, there is something

33
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:48,200
I'd like to discuss with you.

34
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,480
Look, it's like this.

35
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:52,000
Recently our work unit went through restructuring.

36
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,760
But as a senior Party member and veteran cadre,

37
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:56,920
I needed to take the lead, right?

38
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:58,520
So I

39
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:01,160
voluntarily stepped down.

40
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,770
After retiring, I wanted to

41
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:08,200
travel around with my wife.

42
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:10,720
But that's impossible now,

43
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,120
because she has already decided

44
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:14,050
to help you take care of this child.

45
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:17,600
You see, it's become a situation where

46
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,079
she helps you with the child,

47
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:21,720
and I'm left at home with nothing to do.

48
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:24,240
I'm not the type who can stay idle, you know.

49
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,360
I've been working for most of my life, right?

50
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:27,720
But once I'm idle...

51
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:33,680
I understand.

52
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:36,240
Director Jiang, you mean you want

53
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,840
to work at my company, right?

54
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,180
Yes, that's right.

55
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,480
I'm afraid our company might be too small

56
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,520
to accommodate someone of your caliber.

57
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:46,520
Your company isn't small at all.

58
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,480
I've done my research.

59
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:50,079
Your automotive industry

60
00:03:50,079 --> 00:03:52,040
is one of our country's

61
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:54,010
economic hotspots, right?

62
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,440
I really want to

63
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:58,400
learn and improve myself.

64
00:03:58,480 --> 00:03:59,160
Besides,

65
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,680
I have work management experience, right?

66
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:06,520
I can contribute my remaining energy at your company.

67
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:12,200
Alright, I'll think about it.

68
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:14,440
I'll make arrangements at the company tomorrow.

69
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:15,760
That's great, Director Qin!

70
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,839
Just one request - please don't give me any special treatment.

71
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:19,399
I won't.

72
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:37,720
I can't go on.

73
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:49,840
We've made it through a day and night. Just walk a bit more.

74
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,240
I need more.

75
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:56,690
There's only this little left.

76
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:57,730
You drink it.

77
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,000
Aren't you drinking?

78
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:01,900
You have it.

79
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,000
Then I'll drink it.

80
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,320
It's gone.

81
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:15,760
What do we do now?

82
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,820
Give me the bottle.

83
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,200
No, how much further?

84
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:25,800
Look at you, wanting to take a taxi.

85
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,880
Neither of us has a wallet.

86
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:29,740
You don't want the taxi driver to think we're crazy.

87
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:35,280
I can't go on. I really can't walk anymore.

88
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:37,580
If you want to go, go ahead.

89
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:39,080
Wan Xinxin.

90
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,680
Let me be honest with you.

91
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:42,409
I actually admire you. Really.

92
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,680
You have incredibly strong willpower.

93
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,520
Look back.

94
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:47,480
Turn around. Look back.

95
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,480
Look over there.

96
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,720
Look back at the path you've walked.

97
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:52,280
The path you've traveled for a day and night.

98
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:54,280
Do you still think that's a big deal?

99
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:56,010
When we were on that log bridge,

100
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,800
I rushed across quickly.

101
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:58,970
I left you there.

102
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,600
You were scared, weren't you?

103
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,460
But you still made it across, crying and screaming.

104
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,560
What's the big deal?

105
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:08,840
After crossing it, did you still think it was difficult?

106
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:09,520
I left you alone

107
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,720
in that dark cave.

108
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,440
So dark you couldn't see your hand in front of your face.

109
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:15,400
You must have been terrified, right?

110
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:17,440
Screaming like a stuck pig, weren't you?

111
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,840
But you still ran out with your eyes closed.

112
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,280
Xinxin, honestly,

113
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,080
when you've gone through all

114
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,160
these difficulties,

115
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:27,200
look back at what you've overcome.

116
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:30,050
None of it is a big deal. You can get through it all.

117
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,130
Let's go.

118
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,540
I really can't compare to you.

119
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:36,600
You're all muscle.

120
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,170
I really can't match your stamina.

121
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,980
I'm hungry and exhausted now.

122
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:43,880
I really can't walk anymore.

123
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,680
Let me ask you another question.

124
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,159
Do you miss your baby?

125
00:06:51,159 --> 00:06:51,880
I do.

126
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,800
Liu Chang's car is waiting ahead.

127
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:56,600
This pickup system for my training

128
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,360
has all the locations pre-arranged.

129
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:00,240
It's up to you whether to come or not. I'm going ahead.

130
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,280
Really?

131
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:04,600
Are you serious?

132
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,560
Hey, wait for me!

133
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,360
What are you trying to do?

134
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,120
I want to buy a couple of apples.

135
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:32,000
I'll steam them for the child when he wakes up.

136
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,000
I don't have time.

137
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,620
What are you busy with?

138
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,180
I need to go to work.

139
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:39,600
So you're really going to work for Qin Gang?

140
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,960
Don't you feel guilty taking his money?

141
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,130
What's wrong with that?

142
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:46,840
Xu Chunli, you have long hair but short vision.

143
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:50,400
I'm just protecting my nephew's inheritance.

144
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:51,740
Think about it.

145
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,200
You're leaving now?

146
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:55,960
Well...

147
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:58,360
Um... uh...

148
00:07:58,760 --> 00:08:01,000
No, they're playing tricks on me again.

149
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:02,440
All night long,

150
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:06,040
where have Wan Xinxin and that guy gone?

151
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:18,720
Have we reached the top of the mountain?

152
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:21,170
How is it?

153
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:24,180
Not as scary as yesterday, right?

154
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,760
It's really beautiful here.

155
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,080
So you see,

156
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:32,520
as long as you're willing to move forward and climb up,

157
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,720
what awaits you ahead

158
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:36,840
might be challenges or beautiful scenery.

159
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:40,559
Yes, maybe it's difficult.

160
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:44,640
Yes, maybe it's difficult,

161
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,300
but for this possibility,

162
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,120
for a different outcome,

163
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:50,900
it's worth our effort,

164
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,690
worth trying, don't you think?

165
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,040
Old bacon,

166
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,890
I know you're doing all this

167
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,400
just to make me stay.

168
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,360
I'm not doing all this

169
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:05,400
to make you stay.

170
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,400
I just want you to know

171
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:12,200
that as long as we strive to move forward and climb upward,

172
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,320
what awaits us ahead

173
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:18,320
might be beautiful scenery or something wonderful.

174
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:22,440
But I'm still afraid

175
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:25,040
they'll take my precious brother away from me.

176
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,450
Wan Xinxin, listen carefully.

177
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:31,240
If you hold your loved one in your arms,

178
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,480
hold them gently and keep them in your heart,

179
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:37,680
no one can take them away.

180
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,450
Have you noticed this tree?

181
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,320
What kind of tree is this?

182
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,280
This is a wishing tree.

183
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:53,040
It's very powerful around here.

184
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:55,900
Many people have left their beautiful wishes on it.

185
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:58,200
This yellow ribbon

186
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:01,380
represents a beautiful wish.

187
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,800
I have hope again.

188
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:50,680
Back to business.

189
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:53,080
Your position has been arranged.

190
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,080
You can take up the role at our company

191
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,680
as Deputy Director of Sales.

192
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:58,960
Deputy Director.

193
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:02,160
The main thing is to let you get familiar with the business first,

194
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:05,480
and we'll make other arrangements after you're comfortable.

195
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:06,760
As for the compensation,

196
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:09,220
it will be the same as the General Manager's.

197
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,600
That's good.

198
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,200
So...

199
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:16,960
Mr. Jiang.

200
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:22,600
About my mother looking after the child...

201
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:26,080
Mr. Qin, don't worry about that.

202
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,080
You see...

203
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:31,640
Wan Xinxin is too busy with work,

204
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,860
so my wife is the one mainly taking care of the child.

205
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,520
Look, if your mother wants to see the child,

206
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:38,720
she can do so anytime.

207
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:45,000
Yes, but my mother doesn't know

208
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:46,380
about our divorce yet.

209
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,780
Don't worry. It's confidential.

210
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:58,640
But you can't keep a secret forever.

211
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:01,880
You see, my mother has high blood pressure.

212
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,160
I'm afraid if she gets upset,

213
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:06,160
it could trigger a serious episode.

214
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:09,200
She doesn't know

215
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:11,400
that the divorce was because of me.

216
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:11,920
No, no.

217
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:14,240
Mr. Qin, how can you say that?

218
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:15,500
This isn't your fault.

219
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:16,960
It's quite obvious.

220
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:19,520
I know Wan Xinxin quite well.

221
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:21,300
Her temperament is terrible.

222
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:24,840
Anyone who marries her would suffer.

223
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,080
I never expected, truly, Mr. Qin,

224
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:29,720
that your marriage with her could last this long.

225
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:30,560
What does that prove?

226
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:32,160
It proves you're generous and tolerant.

227
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:33,280
You...

228
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,320
Right?

229
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:38,760
Mr. Jiang, you're too good with words.

230
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:41,810
No, it's just the truth.

231
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,400
Well, Mr. Qin, rest assured,

232
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,080
leave this matter to me.

233
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,770
I'll definitely handle it.

234
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:49,120
I believe your mother

235
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,680
will trust what I say.

236
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:54,040
Good.

237
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:57,480
With your help, this will be much easier.

238
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,840
So, Mr. Qin, when should I start?

239
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,080
Anytime.

240
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:15,840
These are already printed.

241
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:18,480
I'll go prepare right away.

242
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:20,480
As soon as possible. Thanks.

243
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:21,440
Thank you.

244
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:36,680
What's wrong?

245
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:40,400
Should I really stay here?

246
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:43,760
If you have doubts...

247
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:46,360
Fine. I'll take you back to the campsite.

248
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:49,000
If you can find your way out of the forest by yourself,

249
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,360
I'll let you leave whenever you want.

250
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:52,280
What do you mean by 'you'll let me'?

251
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:53,280
Whether I stay or go

252
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:54,680
isn't up to you to decide.

253
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,980
But you're right about one thing.

254
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:01,520
When facing difficulties, never look down,

255
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:03,120
because I have a double chin.

256
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:07,180
Now that's the girl I know,

257
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,880
the indestructible, unstoppable, unbreakable

258
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,210
demon queen Wan Xinxin.

259
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:14,880
What?

260
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:30,400
Sis.

261
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:32,480
Sis.

262
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:34,240
Xinxin.

263
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,840
Sis, where's Bao?

264
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:39,380
Keep it down. He just fell asleep.

265
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:40,880
You're finally back.

266
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,210
You had me worried sick.

267
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,080
I'm sorry.

268
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:45,520
Sis.

269
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:49,920
What?

270
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,240
He didn't do anything to you, did he?

271
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:55,300
You've been watching too many TV dramas.

272
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:57,000
I was just worried about you.

273
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,240
You didn't answer your phone all night.

274
00:14:58,240 --> 00:14:59,570
I couldn't sleep at all.

275
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,850
Okay. Thanks for your concern.

276
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:04,080
I'll go check on the baby.

277
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:05,540
Go ahead. He's in the room.

278
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,720
Sis, how about this?

279
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:12,680
If you're tired, you can go home first.

280
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:13,880
I can watch the child.

